daal, separately ‚Ä¢ Keep them on to separate strainers for 10 mins to remove excess water ‚Ä¢ Then spread them onto separate cotton cloths under shadow for 2-3 hrs ‚Ä¢ Then heat up a heavy bottom kadhai, add rice & rosat it until rice changes the color to more whitish, get fluffy, once done take them onto a dry cotton cloth ‚Ä¢ Then into the same kadhai roast chana daal on low flame until they get light grill marks, once done, pour the roasted chana daal onto the roasted rice ‚Ä¢ Then dry roast moong dal followed by the urad daal & take them onto the cotton cloth ‚Ä¢ Then dry roast sabudana & poha separately on low flame & take them out ‚Ä¢ Lastly dry roast cumin seed & coriander seeds & take them out onto the roasted grains ‚Ä¢ Allow the roasted ingredients to cool down completely & them take them to a flour mill & grind fine powder ‚Ä¢ Our chakali bhajani is ready to make crispy chakaliHow to make Kurkurit chakali recipe | how to make bhajanichi chakali recipe | ‚Ä¢ Take the bhajani flour into a large plate or parat. ‚Ä¢ to this add salt, sesame, carom seeds, chilly pw & mix everything well ‚Ä¢ Into a tadaka pan heat up oil, pour this piping hot onto the chakali bhajani flour, mix well & rub the oil all over the flour ‚Ä¢ Heat up some water, once water is about to boil turn off the flame, & knead the dough using hot water ‚Ä¢ carefully mix the flour using a spatula¬† into the hot water, cover it for 10 mins¬† ‚Ä¢ then using lukewarm water knead a tight dough ‚Ä¢ Our chakali dough is ready to make chakali. ‚Ä¢ take some dough from the ready dough, using some water knead the dough to make it soft (as shown in the video) ‚Ä¢ make a log out of it, put the log into the chakali mould, make the chakalis ‚Ä¢ heat up oil for frying the chakali, once oil is med hot, description: Today, in our village, we cook a special thread parotta recipe. This parotta has different names in different places. In Karachi, it is called Lachha Paratha. As a rule, I reach colleges/universities much before my performance time and like to learn and research about what is going on in those bright and Khurafati minds. I also do it for the selfish reason that it takes me back to my own college days when I was one of the most khurafati young men but also, one of the top debaters in the country. I eat at the college canteens and like to attend their after parties if I am invited, P.S: I am always invited :D This bit is part fact, part fiction, but it definitely covers some hilarious incidents that happened along the journey of me doing college festival shows across the country, if you like this one and share it extesively and comment on this one, I shall make this a series and will come up with more in this series, for that, you will have to call me to your college festival this season. I am shameless and selfish, I want great food, great ambience and great agricultural environment around me :D Enjoy Karo Doston !!Credits: Venue courtesy: The Habitat-Comedy and Music CafeShot by: Dishang Popat, Vivian Castelino Harsh Shah and Karan KundnaniLive sound recording: Yash Rajiv Barse, Siegen MoopnarEditor: AnkitSound mixing and mastering: Sreejith MenonWritten and performed by: Sundeep Sharma Special Thanks: Balraj Ghai and Saurabh Bothra for accomodating my requestsSaurabh Pandey for being my contant buddy.Erica for production help.Alina Ali for thumbnail and content supervision.Ojas Entertainment and Rahul Jaiswal for College ShowsZakir Khan, Anubhav Singh Bassi, Samay Raina and Munawwar for allowing me to use their names. tags: homemade brownies|chocolate brownie|brownie recipe|brownie recipe in tamil|fudgy brownie recipe|how to make brownie in tamil|madras samayal|brownie tamil recipe
description: In this video we will see how to make brownie recipe in tamil. There are two types of brownies, cakey brownie which is dry and flaky and fudgy brownie which is softer and more chewy. Both brownies are different in their ratios of flour to fat content. For this recipe, we can use either chocolate bars or chocolate morsels. Also, in this recipe we have used egg but we can make an eggless version by substituting eggs with curd/yogurt.#brownie #brownierecipeintamil #brownierecipe Friends, please do try this brownie recipe at home and share it with your friends and family. Also, please do share your feedback about the recipe in the comments below. All the best and happy cooking!Ingredients:150g semi sweet chocolate or dark chocolate50g Nuts or chocolate1/2 cup Butter (100g)3 Eggs1.5 cup Sugar (300g)1/4 cup Oil1 tsp Vanilla extract1 cup Maida (125 g)1/2 cup cocoa powder (40g)1/8 tsp Salt8 inch square baking pan 175c/350f for 28 min
